snippet.textDisplay: No one asked, but putting 2 zeroes after a version number (12.0.0) is common practice in the software space (called Semantic Versioning or SemVer). The basic idea is to give meaning to the numbers of the version, so that compatible upgrades can be deduced from comparing version numbers, and not by reading release notes or deep diving a wiki.
